                            <comment id="13495641" author="kumarr" created="Mon, 12 Nov 2012 21:10:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trunk: hbase-common/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/util/JVM.java&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495647" author="kumarr" created="Mon, 12 Nov 2012 21:14:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stack, I have attached the patch to this JIRA. As I mentioned in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6965&quot; title=&quot;Generic MXBean Utility class to support all JDK vendors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6965&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6965&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I tried but was unable to implement your recommendation of using ShellCommandExecutor as it&apos;s output is not being parsed by IBM JDK&apos;s Long class. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please review this patch and let me know your comments. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495726" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 12 Nov 2012 22:56:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to do this in 0.94.4. If you need this earlier in 0.94.3, please let me know.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495930" author="stack" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2012 04:22:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kumarr&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kumarr&quot;&gt;Kumar Ravi&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for opening this issue.  Thanks for looking at using hadoop shellcommandexecutor.  It looks like it won&apos;t work for you.  Would suggest that you include in your patch a note to this effect so that the next time someone is reading this code, you&apos;ll answer their question should they have the same thought I had.  I notice the patch includes a new class named JVM.java.  It does not include removal of the old class nor patch to hook up the code to use this new class rather than the one you&apos;d have us remove (do &apos;svn rm&apos; of the old class before making the patch).  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13586754" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 26 Feb 2013 04:54:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This has been riding in 0.94 for too long. Sorry &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kumarr&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kumarr&quot;&gt;Kumar Ravi&lt;/a&gt;, let&apos;s just do this in 0.96.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13621527" author="stack" created="Wed, 3 Apr 2013 23:44:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removing from 0.95.  No progress.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kumarr&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kumarr&quot;&gt;Kumar Ravi&lt;/a&gt; We can bring it back in if you finish this patch (we&apos;d like to work across JVMs)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
